5 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 2-309.11 of Title 47, unless
7 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. Except as otherwise provided by subsection B of this
9 section, commissioned or CLEET-certified agents of the Council on
10 Law Enforcement Education and Training who are hired on or after
11 July 1, 2025, shall participate in and make contributions to the
12 Oklahoma Law Enforcement Retirement System as other participating
13 employers and members of the System. Such employees shall not make
14 contributions to any plan offered by the Oklahoma Public Employees
15 Retirement System, other than the Oklahoma State Employees Deferred
16 Compensation Plan and the Oklahoma State Employees Deferred Savings
17 Incentive Plan. The Council shall be a participating employer in
18 the Oklahoma Law Enforcement Retirement System for all Council on
19 Law Enforcement Education and Training commissioned or CLEET-
20 certified agents who participate in the Oklahoma Law Enforcement
21 Retirement System pursuant to the provisions of this section.
22 B. 1. Commissioned or CLEET-certified agents of the Council on
23 Law Enforcement Education and Training who are retirees of the
24 Oklahoma Law Enforcement Retirement System and who are hired on or
